The dissections confirmed previous morphologic data at E7 .0 -- 7.5 that all Hdhex4/5/Hdhex4 / 5 homozygotes exhibit abnormal morphology , including shortened primitive streak and a lack of morphological head folds or node [ 10,13 ] .
The results of in situ hybridization analysis also confirmed that all three germ layers and extraembryonic tissue are formed in huntingtin deficient embryos .
