The lack of a morphological node and presence of a shortened streak , together with reduced neuroectoderm and lack of headfolds , suggest that anterior streak formation may be impaired in huntingtin deficient embryos .
To investigate this possibility , we examined mesoderm formation in <termsem="SO:0001059"> mutant </term> embryos .
Mesoderm is specified in the <termsem="SO:0001059"> mutant </term> embryos , as marked by the expression of T ( Brachyury ) and Evx1 ( Fig. 2A -- F ) .
